data.content:
verb
/ˈkrɑːsˌbriːd/ -breeds; -bred /-ˌbrɛd/; -breeding
to make two different kinds of animal breed together [+ obj]
crossbreed [=cross, interbreed] sheep [no obj]
Some birds may crossbreed [=interbreed] freely with other species.
[+ obj] :to mix two kinds of plant to form a new one
crossbreed [=cross] wheat and rye
